Zagus Power Systems has said the introduction of the Zektron brand from Turkey into the Nigerian market has continued to provide dependable power solutions to various Nigeria businesses. The company noted in a statement that Zektron Automatic Voltage Regulator was its first product in Nigeria. According to the statement, due to the success of the Zektron voltage stabilisers in Nigeria, it is also pushing its power solution products including uninterruptible power supplies systems, inverters, and surge protection devices, to power businesses in the country. “In about three years of the introduction of the Zektron brand into the Nigerian market, over 1,000 organisations in the manufacturing, education, telecommunications, hospitality, government and private homes are enjoying and benefitting from the innovative Zektron power solution products,” it said. The Sales Director at Zagus Power Systems, Ken Ezeagu, said, “Zektron is a game-changer in the energy industry in Nigeria, catering for the short, medium and long-term power solution needs of corporates and private institutions in the country. “Zektron is doing amazingly well in the Nigerian market. We have since introduced other products including Zektron Uninterruptible Power Supplies Systems, inverters, surge protection device to cater for the needs of business operations in Nigeria as we are projecting over 3,000 Nigerian business organisations will smoothly run their operations using Zektron power solution products. “We are poised to achieving our projections through being continuously innovative and relevant in solving the power challenges in the Nigerian market.”